events.name: Cloud Study Jam Goa
events.description:
Register now for an invite! http://bit.ly/CSJGoa

Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.
Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to complete any labs you want.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Topics:
Machine Learning in Cloud - 9:30 AM - 1:00 PM
Internet of Things in Cloud - 1:30 PM - 5 PM

Lunch will be provided (for attendees of both tracks).

events.name: Quark 2020

venue.name: BITS Pilani K K Birla Goa Campus

events.description:
GDG Goa in collaboration with the organizing committee of Quark 2020, the annual techno-management fest of BITS Pilani K. K. Birla
Goa Campus, would like to invite you for its 14th edition from 31st— 2nd February 2020.
Quark has gone from strength to strength since its inception in 2006 and has made a name for itself as an
avant-garde technical festival, showcasing the latest innovations and hosting pioneers in the fields of
science and technology. With a plethora of events, talks, workshops, and exhibitions, Quark strives to ignite
minds and celebrate a shared passion for knowledge. Quark has been awarded UNESCO, SAYEN, and
CEE patronage, some of the highest forms of support granted to an organization. Quark has had the
pleasure of hosting notable personalities such as the former President of India, Late Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam,
Stephen Pastis, Nobel Laureates Sir Harold Kroto, Dr. John C. Mather, Dr. Robert F. Curl, and Prof
Douglas Osheroff, eminent scientists such as Dr. Chris Phillips, Dr. Vic Hayes, and Dr. Walter Lewin, TV
personalities including Ian McElhinney and many more.
"Phasing through Eons", the theme for Quark 2020, promises a fest like never before. We look forward to
seeing your college actively participate in our fest and join us in this celebration of science and technology.
For more information, please visit fb.com/bitsquark or bits-quark.org.
In case of any queries, feel free to contact the undersigned.

Official Website of Quark'20
https://bits-quark.org/

Registration Link for Quark'20
https://bits-quark.org/register_main/index.html
